{
  "stem": "7455.5",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so-- but we're-- the realization after that pogrom was such that there was no more hope.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I remember when I was in the ghetto, I used to go by the fence and look outside.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Look-- from a distance, we could see the Christian section.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It's like being in a cage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we see there was a girl, mentally retarded, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She was harmless, dancing in the streets and singing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Somebody said she had a disappointed love, and she lost her reason.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We saw from a distance-- from the marketplace there, from our ghetto-- Germans throwing coins at her while she was dancing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I envied her, because they like her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They give her-- they are not going to kill her.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "She could go into the field and lie down and have-- feel the warmth of the sun without fear.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I just ran away from there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I did not like to go to the edge of the ghetto and see that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometimes people said that planes should come down and kill us all, just like Samson and the temple where he died with the Philistines.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If the bombs should destroy the ghetto and all of us-- with the Germans together.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I used to walk away from the ghetto, from the fence, crying.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I said, why am I fighting it so?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Why can't I accept the inevitable, like everybody else?",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
